balance	raw text	cash	doc	5	6	54	55	The impact on the MFI balance sheet liabilities is, however, different because a traditional securitisation without derecognition of the loan typically creates a deposit liability for the full amount of the securitised assets (for the same reason that a repo gives rise to a deposit liability – here, the MFI undertaking the securitisation receives cash, but the loans remain on its balance sheet.																																		
