balance	raw text	comparison	doc	5	6	10	11	98 ECB Manual on MFI balance sheet statistics April 2012 Comparison with loan securitisation in the supervisory framework This section briefly compares the statistical requirements for MFI balance sheet statistics under Regulation ECB/2008/32 with the supervisory requirements for data on securitisation transactions.																																		
balance	raw text	impact	doc	34	35	27	28	Supervisory requirements focus on credit risk transfer by individual credit institutions, while statistical requirements are aimed at providing a comprehensive picture of credit developments regardless of the impact of securitisation deals on the MFI balance sheet in order to enhance macroeconomic and monetary analysis.																																		
balance	raw text	credit risk	doc	16	17	31	57	This is reflected in the requirement that all securitisation transactions are to be recorded for MFI balance sheet statistics, while, according to Annex IX, Part 2 of Directive 2006/48/EC, the originating credit institution engaging in a traditional securitisation may exclude securitised exposures from the calculation of risk-weighted exposure amounts and expected loss amounts if significant credit risk associated with the securitised exposures has been transferred to third parties.27 A further point to underline relates to the coverage of securitisation transactions under the two reporting frameworks.																																		
balance	raw text	risk	doc	3	4	54	55	In contrast, MFI balance sheet statistics do not cover synthetic securitisation, as this has no impact on outstanding amounts of credit.28 Moreover, securitisation transactions are disclosed for supervisory purposes whether or not they are set up using a securitisation special purpose entity (SSPE) because of the importance for prudential purposes of recording transfers of risk which in turn affect capital requirements.																																		
balance	raw text	regulation	doc	8	9	23	24	In contrast, the definition of securitisation in MFI balance sheet statistics covers only securitisation transactions undertaken using SSPEs or FVCs.29 The requirements of Regulation ECB/2008/32, however, also cover other types of loan transfer																																		
balance	raw text	regulation	doc	17	18	13	14	Tranching is not, however, a necessary condition for inclusion in statistical reporting under Regulation ECB/2008/32, so MFI balance sheet statistics may include securitisation transactions that are not tranched and thus not compliant with the supervisory requirements.																																		
balance	raw text	pool	doc	44	45	29	30	In contrast to the case of securitisation, covered bonds are debt securities issued by a credit institution directly (or fully guaranteed by a credit institution) and covered by a pool of loans (typically mortgage loans) or public sector debt which do not leave the balance sheet of the issuer.																																		
