balance	raw text	valuation	doc	14	15	29	30	The most important definitional and conceptual departures from the ESA 95 in the MFI balance sheet statistics are the treatment of interest accruing on deposits and loans and the valuation of securities (both of these issues are mentioned in earlier sections of this manual – see, for instance, Section 2.1), and the difficulty in linking some																																		
balance	raw text	market	doc	30	31	48	49	“remaining assets” or “remaining liabilities”, not in the relevant instrument category, as the ESA 95 prefers.5 Furthermore, in order to enable accounting information to be used for statistical purposes, MFI balance sheet statistics allow discretion in the valuation of securities, whereas the ESA 95 requires the use of market prices for both transactions and positions.6																																		
